title: For Sale:  M1911 A1 US Army Issue 1945 Ithica Colt Marked works very well WW 2 History Piece
postcontent: This is a nice piece of WW2 History. US Army Government issue M 1911 A1 45 ACP Pistol. I've researched this and it is an Ithica model made between 1944 and 1945. All the proof marks are there. It was assembled and proofed by Ithica. There are approximatedly 335,000 of these made during the war. As the need arose for more weapons during the war many of the guns were assembled using Colt parts by MFG's such as Ithica, Sears, Remington, and Colt.This .45 is fully marked and in nice condition for the age. It's been fully serviced by a gunsmith and is in great operable condition. I just cleaned this gun after running about a 1/2 a box of shells through it with no issues. It shoots a nice grouping at 20 yards. Comes with a new 8 rd. magazine. Sights have been replaced and set for 20 yard shots. The barrel was replaced. Original barrel is included but is not useable. If you are looking for a nice WW2 conversation piece that is reliable and works, here's your chance.
